ce:section.ce:para:
25,26,27,28-tetra(1-butyloxy)calix[4]arene (1,3-

   alternate

) (2a): The 1,3-alternate conformer of calix[4]arene 2a was prepared according to a slightly modified literature procedure [30,48]. A mixture of 1 (1.7 g, 4 mmol) and Cs2CO3 (9.8 g, 30 mmol) in DMF (60 ml) was heated at 80 °C for 60 min. Subsequently, n-butyl tosylate (11 g, 48 mmol) was added and the heating at 80 °C was continued during next 24 h. Solvent residues were removed at 70 °C in vacuo. After addition of CH2Cl2 (50 ml), the reaction mixture was poured onto 2 M HCl solution (100 ml). The organic layer being washed by 5% NaCl (3 × 30 ml) was concentrated by distillation. Then a crude product was stirred in a boiling MeOH, with matured precipitate being filtered off and dried under reduced pressure at 100 °C. Yield: 0.99 g (38%). 1H NMR spectrum characteristics of the synthesized 2a are in accordance with literature data [49].

25,26,27,28-tetra(1-dodecyloxy)calix[4]arene (1,3-

   alternate

) (2b): Compound 2b was prepared similarly to the compound 2a using n-dodecyl tosylate (16.3 g, 48 mmol) which was obtained previously by tosylation of C12H25OH with TsCl in CHCl3/Pyridine. The crude product was stirred in the acetone applied instead of MeOH. The matured precipitate was filtered off and dried under reduced pressure at 100 °C. Yield: 2.59 g (59%). Mp. = 101 °С. Anal. calcd for C76H120O4 (1097.79) %: C, 83.15; H 11.02. Found: C, 83.34; H, 10.89.

5,11,17,23-tetra-(chloromethyl)-25,26,27,28-tetra(1-butyloxy)calix[4]arene (1,3

   -alternate

) (3a): Chloromethyl methyl ether (47.5 mmol, 7.4 ml (6.3 M/l)) was added to the calix[4]arene 2a (0.78 g, 1.19 mmol) in a dry chloroform (40 ml) under argon atmosphere. The reaction mixture was cooled down to − 40 °С. Tin tetrachloride (0.84 ml, 7.2 mmol) was added dropwise under vigorous stirring. Stirring was continued for 30 min at − 40 °С. After stirring the reaction mixture at ambient temperature during next 40 min, the cold water (80 ml) was added. The organic layer being separated was washed twice with water (25 ml). Then it was dried over MgSO4 and concentrated by distillation in vacuo. The target calix[4]arene 3a was obtained with yield 67% (0.67 g). Mp. 219 ºC. Anal. calcd for C48H60Cl4O4 (842.80) %: С, 68.41; H, 7.18; Cl, 16.82. Found %: C, 68.35; H, 7.02; Cl, 16.97.

5,11,17,23-tetra-(chloromethyl)-25,26,27,28-tetra(1-dodecyloxy)calix[4]arene (1,3

   -alternate

) (3b): Compound 3b was prepared similarly to the compound 3a using calix[4]arene 2b (1.31 g, 1.19 mmol). The crude product was dissolved in a hot acetone and cooled down to 5 °С. The precipitate formed was filtered off and dried at room temperature. The target calix[4]arene 3b was obtained as a pale yellow powder with yield 50% (0.76 g). Mp. 97–99 °C Anal. calcd for C80H124Br2Cl4O4 (1288.83) %: С, 74.39; H, 9.68; Cl, 10.98. Found %: C, 74.21; H, 9.84; Cl, 10.75.

5,11,17,23-tetra-[(acetylaceton-3-yl)methyl)]-25,26,27,28-tetra(1-butyloxy)-calix[4]arene (1,3

   -alternate

) (4a): To solution of the compound 3a (0.59 g, 0.7 mmol) in the mixture of acetone (12 ml) and DMF (6 ml), the NaAA (0.53 g, 4.27 mmol) and NaI (0.64 g, 4.27 mmol) were added. The reaction mixture was stirring during 1 day at 60 °С under argon atmosphere. After cooling, CH2Cl2 (25 ml) and 1 М HCl (25 ml) were added under stirring to the mixture. The organic layer being separated was washed twice with water (25 ml) and 10% Na2S2O3 (20 ml). Then it was dried over MgSO4 and concentrated by distillation in vacuo. The target calix[4]arene 4a was obtained with yield 60% (0.46 g) as a viscous pale brown oil. IR (nujol, cm−1): ν 3380, 3180 (ν(OH)), 1722, 1698 (νС=О), 1602 (ν(С=О) and ν(С=С)), 1463 (ν(Ph)), 1377, 1356, 1215, 1146 (νas(CCC)), 950 (νs (CCC)). C68H88O12 (1097.44). Anal. calcd for C68H88O12 (1097.44) %: C, 74.42; H, 8.08. Found, %: C, 74.22; H, 8.18. Мass spectrum (MALDI-TOF): m/z 1115 [M+H2O+H]+.

5,11,17,23-tetra-[(acetylaceton-3-yl)methyl)]-25,26,27,28-tetra(1-dodecyloxy)-calix[4]arene (1,3

   -alternate

) (4b): Compound 4b was prepared similarly to the compound 4a using calix[4]arene 3b (0.9 g, 0.7 mmol), with a time of reaction being increased up to 4 days. The target calix[4]arene 4b was obtained with yield 49% (0.59 g) as a viscous pale brown oil. IR (nujol, cm−1): ν 3538, 3410, 3199, (ν(OH)), 1726, 1701 (ν(С=О)), 1603 (ν(С=О) и ν(С=С)), 1466 (ν(Ph)), 1380, 1356, 1218, 1146 (νas(CCC)), 949 (νs(CCC)). Anal. calcd for C100H152O12 (1546.30) %: C, 77.68; H, 9.91. Found, %: C, 77.82; H, 9.79. Мass spectrum (MALDI-TOF): m/z: 1569 [M+Na]+, 1584 [M+K]+.

5,17-dibromo-25,26,27,28-tetra(1-butyloxy)calix[4]arene (1,3

   -alternate

) (7): The Cs2CO3 salt (2.93 g, 9 mmol) was added to solution of the compound 6 (1 g, 1.5 mmol) in DMF (20 ml). The reaction mixture was stirring during 1 h at 80 °С under argon atmosphere. After addition of bromobutane C4H9Br (1.2 ml, 9 mmol), the reaction mixture was stirring during 72 h at 80 оС. Then, a solvent was removed and the residue was redisolved in CH2Cl2 (40 ml). The organic layer being washed twice with 3 M HCl (2 ×40 ml) and water (2 ×100 ml) was dried over MgSO4. Then it was concentrated by distillation in vacuo. The crude product was stirring in the boiled MeOH and filtered. The target calix[4]arene 7 was obtained with yield 69% (0.84 g).1H NMR spectrum characteristics of the synthesized 7 are in accordance with literature data [32].

5,17-dibromo-11,23-bis-(chloromethyl)-25,26,27,28-tetra(1-butyloxy)calix[4]arene (

   1,3-alternate

) (8): Compound 8 was prepared similarly to the compound 3b using calix[4]arene 7 (0.89 g, 1.19 mmol). The target calix[4]arene 8 was obtained as a pale yellow powder with yield 81% (0.87 g). Mp. 132–134 °C. Anal. calcd for C46H56Br2Cl2O4 (903.19) %: С, 61.14; H, 6.25. Found %: C, 61.37; H, 6.32.

5,17-dibromo-11,23-bis-[(acetylaceton-3-yl)methyl]-25,26,27,28-tetra(1-butyloxy)calix[4]arene (1,3

   -alternate

) (9): Compound 9 was prepared similarly to the compound 4a using calix[4]arene 8 (0.64 g, 0.7 mmol), with a time of reaction being increased up to 3 days. The target calix[4]arene 9 was obtained with yield 68% (0.49 g) as a viscous brown oil. IR (in a thin layer, cm−1): ν 3527, 3414, (ν(OH)), 1713, 1702 (ν(С=О)), 1605 (ν(С=О) и ν(С=С)), 1459 (ν(Ph)), 1379, 1358, 1212, 1153 (νas(CCC)), 955 (νs(CCC)). Anal. calcd for C56H70Br2O8 (1030.98) %: C, 65.24; H, 6.48; Br, 15.50. Found, %: C 65.39; H 6.72; Br, 15.28. Мass spectrum (MALDI-TOF): m/z: 1047.34 [M+H2O+H]+.
